While engaged in boycotts in Mississippi, Charles Evers stated that if anyone broke the boycott against discriminatory businesses, he'd have them killed.  &quot;If we catch any of you going in any of them racist stores, we're gonna break your damn neck.&quot;  This &quot;threat&quot; was found not to be actionable under the US Constitution.  It was a heck of a lot more serious than anything that has been said on a message board, especially due to the intimate knowledge of the people involved and the violence present.<br>
